---
import PageShell from "../components/PageShell.astro";

const privacyBreadcrumbs = [
  { name: "Home", path: "/" },
  { name: "Privacy Policy", path: "/privacy/" },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Al Tareen collects, uses, and protects your information."
  keywords="Al Tareen privacy policy, cookies, data collection, consent preferences, website privacy"
  hidePageHead={false}
  breadcrumbs={privacyBreadcrumbs}
>
  <section class="legalPage" aria-label="Privacy Policy">
    <div class="legalContainer">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="effective">Effective Date: March 25, 2026</p>

      <p>
        At <strong>Al Tareen</strong> (https://altareen.com), your privacy is treated
        with clarity and respect. This policy explains what data is collected,
        how it is used, and how you remain in control.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Contact Data:</strong> Name, email address, and any information
          you provide when submitting forms.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Usage Interactions:</strong> Anonymous framework feedback
          (likes/dislikes) stored in aggregated form.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Technical Data:</strong> Basic request data such as IP address,
          browser type, and device information.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Cookies & Consent</h2>
      <p>
        This website uses a consent-based system for cookies and tracking.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          If you <strong>accept</strong>, certain non-essential features such as
          analytics or preference storage may be enabled.
        </li>
        <li>
          If you <strong>decline</strong>, no non-essential cookies or tracking
          technologies are stored.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        A minimal record of your consent choice is stored locally in your browser
        to ensure your preference is respected.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Feedback System (Likes / Dislikes)</h2>
      <p>
        When interacting with framework feedback:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Votes are stored in aggregated form on the server</li>
        <li>No personal identity is associated with votes</li>
        <li>
          If cookies are declined, your vote is not stored in a way that persists
          across sessions
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. How Your Information Is Used</h2>
      <p>Your data is used to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to inquiries</li>
        <li>Improve website functionality and content</li>
        <li>Understand general usage patterns (if consent is provided)</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Your information is <strong>never sold, rented, or traded</strong>.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        Certain features (such as contact forms) may rely on third-party services.
        These services may process submitted data according to their own policies.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Data Storage</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Feedback counts are stored server-side in aggregated form</li>
        <li>Consent preferences are stored locally in your browser</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Data is retained only as long as necessary for functionality,
        communication, or legal compliance.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You may request:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access to your data</li>
        <li>Deletion of submitted information</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Contact:
        <a href="mailto:altareenk@outlook.com">altareenk@outlook.com</a>
      </p>

      <h2>9. External Links</h2>
      <p>
        This website may contain links to third-party sites. We are not responsible
        for their privacy practices.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. Continued use of the site
        constitutes acceptance of updates.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy-related inquiries:
        <a href="mailto:altareenk@outlook.com">altareenk@outlook.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>


<style is:global>
  html, body {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .legalPage {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: var(--content-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 0 64px;
    display: flow-root;
  }

  .legalContainer {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: var(--content-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 24px;
    border-radius: 16px;
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--border) 74%, transparent);
    background:
      linear-gradient(
        180deg,
        color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface) 98%, white 2%),
        color-mix(in srgb, var(--surface) 98%, black 2%)
      );
    box-shadow:
      0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.62) inset,
      0 8px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.018);
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .effective {
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--ink-muted);
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 22px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  p {
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0 0 12px 18px;
    padding: 0;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
  }

  a {
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
  }

  a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--ink-muted);
  }

  /* Fix header logo unwanted styling */
  header a,
  .logo {
    border: none !important;
    background: transparent !important;
    box-shadow: none !important;
  }

  /* Remove underline from footer links */
  footer a {
    text-decoration: none !important;
    border-bottom: none !important;
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .legalContainer {
      padding: 16px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
    }
  }
</style>
</PageShell>